What is Self-Attention?

Self-Attention is a mechanism that allows a model to focus on different parts of the same input sequence when making predictions.

Instead of processing words one by one like traditional RNNs, self-attention looks at the entire sequence at once and decides:

"Which words are important for understanding this word?"

🧠 Intuition

Consider the sentence:

"The cat sat on the mat because it was tired."

What does "it" refer to?

To understand this, the model must look back at previous words.
Self-attention helps the model learn that "it" → "cat", not "mat".

It assigns higher importance (attention weight) to relevant words.

⚙️ How Self-Attention Works (Step-by-Step)

For each word in a sentence:

1️⃣ Create Three Vectors

Each word is converted into:

Query (Q) → What am I looking for?

Key (K) → What do I contain?

Value (V) → What information do I give?

These are created using learned weight matrices.
